hs, we have code that aliases `String#to_i` to `String#to_int`\n\nTurns out that having this line\n\n```\n  String.send(:alias_method, :to_int, :to_i)\n```\n\nincluded in the project, and then `require`ing the file before running the specs is enough to cause the rspec runner to hang when an exception is raised _in any other spec_. Running the specs from the command line via `rspec` will run them all, but the process will hang for every format type; running the specs in Textmate will bollux up the display and hang the progress bar, overwrite all kinds of text... loads of fun.\n\nThis happens (at least) using rspec-2.0.X, running this sample spec file\n\nhttp://gist.github.com/634357\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/195/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/195/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}